longBusinessSummary: iPure Labs, Inc., an exploration stage company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, development, and production of oil and gas projects. It holds interest in Huaya Anticline project, a block 100 oil prospect located in the Ucayali Basin, Peru; and Bosques block, comprising approximately 9,000 hectares located in the Middle Magdalena Valley of Colombia. The company also holds interests in Junction prospect, covering approximately 500 acres located in northwestern Cherokee County, approximately five miles southwest of Jacksonville, Texas; Northwest Jacksonville prospect, covering approximately 350 acres located in northern Cherokee County; and Highway 79 prospect, covering approximately 340 net acres located in northwestern Cherokee County, one mile west of Jacksonville, Texas. The company was incorporated as in 2000 and is based in Henderson, Nevada.
